    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "No. We don't plan IPC. \r\nBecause actually Erigon's memory has nothing useful - there is no blocks, no trie, no txpool. And RPCDaemon has nothing as well.\r\nEverything is in DB or in another Services. \r\nBut our DB allows multiple readers in same time - and they will share OS's PageCache. \r\nAlso most of services have gRpc interface - but it doesn't look like \"json rpc\".\r\n\r\nAlso, do you have proof that your bottleneck is \"websocket/json\"?\r\n\r\n",
